class DenseNet[source]

DenseNet(growth_rate=32, block_config=(6, 12, 24, 16), num_init_features=64, bn_size=4, drop_rate=0, num_classes=1000) :: Module

Densenet-BC model class, based on "Densely Connected Convolutional Networks" <https://arxiv.org/pdf/1608.06993.pdf>_

Args: growth_rate (int) - how many filters to add each layer (k in paper) block_config (list of 4 ints) - how many layers in each pooling block num_init_features (int) - the number of filters to learn in the first convolution layer bn_size (int) - multiplicative factor for number of bottle neck layers (i.e. bn_size * k features in the bottleneck layer) drop_rate (float) - dropout rate after each dense layer num_classes (int) - number of classification classes
